author: Daily News staff
title: COS volleyball squad wins league opener vs. Lassen
text: COS volleyball squad wins league opener vs. Lassen Comment   By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 12:46 PM By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 12:46 PM WEED The College of the Siskiyous volleyball squad opened Golden Valley Conference play with a four set win over Lassen in Weed on Friday. The Lady Eagles won 25-9, 22-25, 25-12, 25-19. COS is now 15-3 overall and are in the middle of a 12-game win streak. Kelsey Loyd led COS with 27 kills, while Weed High School grad Marielle Schnack had 12 kills. Alissa Flynn finished with 17 digs for the Lady Eagles, while Gisela Martin had 15 digs. Weed High School grad Jillian Neel led COS with 25 assists, while Mount Shasta grad Alex Peruzzi led COS with four service aces. On Wednesday, COS is at Shasta and faces Redwoods on Friday at home at 4 p.m. By Daily News staff   By Daily News staff
